photometry.remarks:
Stuart Parker, Canterbury, New Zealand, reports the discovery of an apparent supernova (red mag 13.0) on a 30-s unfiltered CCD image (limiting mag 16.5) 
taken by himself with a 30-cm Astro-Tech AT12RC Ritchey-Chretien astrograph (+ ST10 camera) at his Parkdale Observatory in the course of the Backyard Observatory Supernova Search.Which is 12W"and 196N"of the nucleus of the galaxy NGC7424 
This is a very early morning target
[Last non detection] last seasons image nothing visible
